Hello readers,
My name is Andraž Đurič, and I developed the Story Engine architecture you're about to use.


What This Is:
The Story Engine is a formal specification for stateful narrative simulation using large language models.
It transforms AI from an improvisational storyteller into a coherent simulation engine; maintaining hidden state, enforcing consequences,
tracking complex systems, and generating emergent narratives that feel alive.
This isn't "AI writing a story." This is a world simulator that happens to express itself through narrative.


Why I Built This:
Two sparks:
 A small, practical one: I was reading a physical book in a dim room, too lazy to stand up and switch on the light. 
 I used my phone as a makeshift lamp. It was annoying. I thought: why can’t I just read this—beautifully—on the phone? 
 Yes, e-books exist, but I couldn’t justify the spend at the time. 
 That irritation nudged a bigger idea: 
 what about endless, personalized stories in linguistic form, powered by AI?
 
 A larger, philosophical one: I believe interactive, meaningful entertainment shouldn’t be gatekept by money or specialized tooling. 
 With AI improving year over year, we’re edging toward abundant, individually tailored experiences—and, more broadly,
 a plausible path toward post-scarcity dynamics. My hunch: the “last” product capitalism invests in is the one
 that makes it obsolete; AI/AGI may be that product. Time will tell.

Today’s AI storytelling often drifts, forgets, and contradicts itself. Structure helps. 
This project is a demonstration that careful specification and system design can lift consistency and depth without expensive infrastructure. 
The first version came together in under an hour (not counting testing); several iterations later, you’re seeing a cleaner, sturdier form.


The Mission:
Make narrative simulation accessible to everyone.

This means:
Writers can create complex interactive fiction without coding
Educators can build historical simulations without game engines
Players can experience deep, reactive stories without $60 price tags
Communities can collaborate on shared worlds without corporate gatekeeping
Multilingual creators can build authentic cultural experiences


